<TITLE> Depression likely to move in </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 6 (bdnews24.com)The land depression over the coastal areas of West Bengal and adjoining Bangladesh moved slightly north- northwestwards and now lies over West Bengal and adjoining area, the Met Office said on Sunday. It is likely to move in a north-northwesterly direction further inland and weaken gradually. Under its influence steep pressure gradient persist over North Bay. Monsoon is moderate to strong over North Bay. Squally weather may affect the maritime ports and the coastal regions of Bangladesh. Capital Dhaka and other parts of the country may also experience moderate to heavy rainfall on Sunday. Maritime ports of Chittagong, CoxS Bazar and Mongla have been advised to keep hoisted local cautionary signal number three three. All fishing boats and trawlers over North Bay have been advised to proceed with caution but not to venture into the deep sea. bdn
